Cingulate cortex.EditorialNote: The only elements labelled "cingulate cortex" in neuronames related to mouse brain parcellations both from Swanson and from Paxinos.  No "cingulate cortex" is listed for primates.  There are the many cortical areas defined by Brodmann's parcellation scheme present in NeuroNames, and they are obviously the mans by which cortical parenchyma regions are accessed. (BB).
